# Compare addresses with `isAddressEqual`

To compare two EVM addresses, use viem's `isAddressEqual`. Never compare with `===`/`!==` on
`.toLowerCase()`d strings. EIP-55 casing is only a checksum for typo detection — it is not part of an
address's identity — so comparisons must be case-insensitive, and `isAddressEqual` also validates
that both operands are well-formed addresses.

```ts
import { isAddressEqual } from 'viem';

// ❌ BAD — manual lowercasing, no validation
if (log.address.toLowerCase() === gateway.toLowerCase()) { /* ... */ }

// ✅ GOOD
if (isAddressEqual(log.address, gateway)) { /* ... */ }
```

This applies to comparisons only. `.toLowerCase()` is still fine for normalizing an address before
storage (e.g. a DB column whose CHECK requires lowercase). It does NOT apply to non-address values
like tx hashes or `bytes32` ids — compare those with a lowercased/normalized equality as usual.
